  "text": "The 71.6 kDa protein is similar to the members of the molybdopterin oxidoreductase family, primarily to formate dehydrogenases. It contains one [FeS] cluster binding motif and a molybdopterin cofactor binding site. It is to note, that in many hyperthermophilic archaeal oxidoreductases the molybdenum is replaced by tungsten [CITATION_1] .",
